com.googlecode.cqengine.codegen

Class AttributeBytecodeGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.codegen.AttributeBytecodeGenerator

  • public class AttributeBytecodeGenerator
extends Object
    Generates Attributes by synthesizing bytecode, avoiding the need to write attributes by hand. The synthesized attributes should perform as well at runtime as hand-written ones in most cases.

    Note this class uses the javassist library to generate bytecode, which is an optional dependency in CQEngine's pom.xml. If you wish to use this class, ensure that you re-declare the dependency on javassist again in your application's pom.xml.

    Generated attributes are loaded into the ClassLoader of the given POJO classes.

        public static <O,A> Class<? extends SimpleAttribute<O,A>> generateSimpleAttributeForField(Class<O> pojoClass,
                                                                          Class<A> attributeValueType,
                                                                          String fieldName,
                                                                          String attributeName)
        Generates a SimpleAttribute which reads a non-null value from the given field in a POJO.

        The type of value returned by the attribute should match the type of the field. However reading primitive values is also supported. In that case, the attribute will box the primitive value to its wrapper type automatically, and so the type of the attribute itself should be the wrapper type.

        Type Parameters:
        O - Type of the POJO object
        A - The type of value returned by the attribute
        Parameters:
        pojoClass - The class containing the field
        attributeValueType - The type of value returned by the attribute
        fieldName - The name of the field
        attributeName - The name to give to the attribute
        Returns:
        A generated class for an attribute which reads from the POJO as discussed above

      • generateMultiValueAttributeForField

        public static <O,A> Class<? extends MultiValueAttribute<O,A>> generateMultiValueAttributeForField(Class<O> pojoClass,
                                                                                  Class<A> attributeValueType,
                                                                                  String fieldName,
                                                                                  String attributeName)
        Generates a MultiValueAttribute which reads non-null values from the given field in a POJO.

        The type of values returned by the attribute should match the type of values stored in the field. The field may be a List or an array, of objects of the same type as the attribute. However reading from primitive arrays is also supported. In that case, the attribute will box the primitive values to their wrapper type automatically, and so the type of the attribute itself should be the wrapper type.

        Type Parameters:
        O - Type of the POJO object
        A - The type of values returned by the attribute
        Parameters:
        pojoClass - The class containing the field
        attributeValueType - The type of values returned by the attribute
        fieldName - The name of the field
        attributeName - The name to give to the attribute
        Returns:
        A generated class for an attribute which reads from the POJO as discussed above
